# Server protection

- Firewall Applicatif (WAF) anti XSS, anti Sql Injection (ex: ModSecurity, NAXSI, raptor_waf)
- IPS (Instrusion Prevention System) (ex: Fail2ban, snort)
- IDS réseau (ex: maltrail, snort)
- IDS systeme (ex: Chkrootkit, rkhunter)
- HIDS (OSSEC)
- Firewall (ex: iptables, arno-iptables-firewall)
- Audit tool: Lynis
- Install cleaner (ccleaner, bleachbit)
- Anti-DDOS Tool: https://github.com/fnzv/nShield, https://securityonline.info/15-things-prevent-ddos-attacks/
- AV: clamav, metadefender.com, virustotal.com, nodistribute.com, ovs.acunetix.com
- Database Firewall: DBShield
- Backup auto with encryption
- Block iframe (add_header X-Frame-Options Deny;)
- Block clickjacking attack (anti-clickjacking X-Frame-Options header)
- XSS Protection header (X-XSS-Protection)
- Content-Security-Policy header
- Secure cookie flag to only authorize https
- Block Bad bot (SetEnvIfNoCase ^User-Agent$ .*(libwww-perl|aesop_com_spiderman) HTTP_SAFE_BADBOT)
- Filter ip access
- Certificats SSL
- isoler les serveur au sein d'un réseau privé (vRack)
- Port knocking
- Disabled ssh password access and add ssh key
- High Availability
- Passphrases instead off password
- Disable error_reporting
- Hide verbose informations (apache, php, mysql versions etc..)
- One user by application
- DNS(sec) (block spoofing dns)
- keepass
- Apparmor
- Keep eyes on logs
- Double authentification
- Prevent RFI attack
- [Security Checklist](http://bit.ly/2lLWFVF)
- [Security guide](https://github.com/forter/security-101-for-saas-startups)
- [How to Secure and Harden Cloud/VPS VM](https://geekflare.com/cloud-vm-security-guide/)
- Check files integrity
- Remove metadatas (mat)
- Code review/code analyser: RIPS
- Remove Leak information like server header
- Prevent cross site attacks using same site cookies
- Prevent ARP-spoofing: https://github.com/europa502/shARP
- Find malware
- SIEM / SOC
- https://github.com/evilsocket/opensnitch
- https://github.com/yandex/gixy
- gravityscan.com
- https://simplesecurity.sensedeep.com/web-developer-security-checklist-f2e4f43c9c56

# How to respond to an attack ?

- Put website offline
- Change all passwords
- Remove all files
- Reinstall a clean copy
- Upgrade all plugins

# Wifi Defense

1 – Rebaptiser le nom de votre réseau Wifi
2 – Changer tous les mois le mot de passe de votre routeur Wifi
3 – S’assurer que le mot de passe Wifi est en WPA2-PSK
4 – Régler le filtrage des adresses MAC
5 – Mettre en place un VPN
6 – Régler la portée du signal Wifi
